• I verified it ground-up and found the real reason: after the cleanup, the architecture was mostly native data-theme, but the production CSS still did not map the Theme Test Lab behavior onto Frappe’s real DOM deeply enough.

  The lab styles simple demo classes like .sb-item, tr.interactive, .table-wrap, .tree-row. Frappe uses different nested structures:

  - Sidebar text is on .standard-sidebar-item > a.item-anchor, .sidebar-item-label, .sidebar-item-icon
  - List row borders are on .list-row-border, not only .list-row
  - Report tables use .datatable, .dt-cell, .dt-cell__content, and CSS variables like --dt-cell-bg
  - Child tables use .grid-row, .data-row, .grid-static-col

  So backgrounds matched because tokens and container selectors worked. Hover text, borders, shadows, and table cells failed because Frappe paints those on deeper child elements.

